what to do when you've never had any experience responsibility in life then you're suddenly told to 'grow up' from being knee high i've never been given any responsiblity was never allowed to socialise wasn't trusted was verbally abused stopped from having male friends at now i'm at the stage where it is all catching up with me i have depression and agoraphobia and have quit university because i cannot cope my parents cannot seem to grasp that they have a small role to play in my fate how can they expect me to be a fully functional adult when i have not been allowed to develop i accept that i hold a lot of the responsibility now for giving up and allowing myself to be treated like i was but i have no self esteem left so i really do not know what to do or where to go from here i have seriously underdeveloped speaking and social skills and i'm not sure how to improve these is it possible to develop skills like this late on in life or do you think that there comes a point where you have to accept your shortfalls and get on with it where do i start with this it is time for you to take control of your life if you don't like it you are the only one who can change it your parents did their job albeit not a good one in your eyes but they were probably doing all they knew how to do you will probably not be able to acknowledge this while you are still in victim mode you could spend the rest of your life blaming them but who are you hurting you ask how can they expect me to be a fully functional adult etc it is not about them it's about what you should expect from yourself this is where you get your self esteem they seem to be oblivious to it are you going to let it control you one more day i would start by seeking counseling you have some deep seated issues that a good counselor can bring out into the open try county offices if you are strapped for cash they are very affordable based on income level a great book to start your healing process is your inner child of the past yo